<TITLE> DU's 45th convocation set for Dec 12 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 5 (bdnews24.com)  Dhaka University will hold its 45th convocation on Dec 12 this year, university authorities announced on Saturday. The decision came from a preparatory meeting, chaired by DU vice chancellor AAMS Arefin Siddique, , a statement of the university said. The university would confer an honorary doctor of science degree on Yuan T Lee, who shared a Nobel Prize with two others in chemistry in 1986, on the day. Lee is also invited to be the convocation speaker. Former DU student in chemistry Abul Hussam, who is the inventor of the 'Sono' arsenic filter, and historian Ranajit Guha will also be endowed with honorary doctor of science and doctor of literature degrees respectively. Students wishing to be present at the convocation were asked to register by Oct 20 this year. Those who have already registered for the convocation do not need to do so again. Those having completed their graduations since the 44th convocation, and registered for the postponed 45th convocation, may register. The university held its 44th convocation on Apr 7 in 2008. The 45th convocation was originally scheduled to be held in February this year
